1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:02,000
We could get D'Angelo flowers.

2
00:00:02,000 --> 00:00:06,000
No, you can't get flowers for someone who's in a coma that won't before he wakes up.

3
00:00:06,000 --> 00:00:07,000
Yeah, that's true.

4
00:00:07,000 --> 00:00:11,000
All in favor of the baskets full of chocolates, teddy bears, and balloons?

5
00:00:11,000 --> 00:00:19,000
Wait, wait. All in favor of the knapsack filled with canned goods, chainsaw, gasoline, and emergency radio in case he wakes up post-apocalypse?

6
00:00:22,000 --> 00:00:23,000
Nope, baskets have it.

7
00:00:23,000 --> 00:00:29,000
So as it turns out, unless you're a young child or a prison inmate, you don't need anyone supervising you.

8
00:00:30,000 --> 00:00:33,000
People just come in and do their work on their schedule.

9
00:00:33,000 --> 00:00:40,000
Imagine that. People like us allowed to sell paper, unsupervised, and yet somehow it works.

10
00:00:40,000 --> 00:00:42,000
Must be because the stakes are so high.

11
00:00:43,000 --> 00:00:47,000
Well, I really appreciate the offer, but I'm just happy the way things are.

12
00:00:48,000 --> 00:00:50,000
Okay. Thank you.

13
00:00:51,000 --> 00:00:56,000
That was Joe asking me if I wanted to take over as acting manager while they find a replacement.

14
00:00:56,000 --> 00:01:01,000
I told her I don't want to mess this up, right? There's a consensus. People are happy.

15
00:01:07,000 --> 00:01:08,000
Dwight Schrute?

16
00:01:12,000 --> 00:01:13,000
Yes, I would.

17
00:01:15,000 --> 00:01:16,000
Thank you.

18
00:01:17,000 --> 00:01:21,000
Jordan, gather my things from my desk.

19
00:01:26,000 --> 00:01:27,000
Wait.

20
00:01:32,000 --> 00:01:33,000
What have you done?

21
00:01:37,000 --> 00:01:41,000
Rose, you'll never guess where I am right now.

22
00:01:56,000 --> 00:01:57,000
I'm sorry.

23
00:02:26,000 --> 00:02:27,000
You can't stay there all day.

24
00:02:28,000 --> 00:02:29,000
I'm coming.

25
00:02:31,000 --> 00:02:33,000
Do I at least get to go with you in this fantasy?

26
00:02:34,000 --> 00:02:35,000
You'll slow me down.

27
00:02:36,000 --> 00:02:39,000
Dwight has been acting manager for three months now?

28
00:02:40,000 --> 00:02:43,000
Nope, a week. Just feels like three months.

29
00:02:43,000 --> 00:02:50,000
Let's see. We all have to punch into a time clock, which is very old, very strong, and has the slot about the size of a finger.

30
00:02:50,000 --> 00:02:58,000
We were all given new business cards, big enough to set us apart from the competition, which is how I learned that our titles are all now junior employee.

31
00:02:59,000 --> 00:03:09,000
Our lunch breaks are staggered to prevent wasting time. Mine's at 10.30, and I find that the first hour of the day goes by a lot quicker than the second seven hours.

32
00:03:10,000 --> 00:03:11,000
Stop stalling.

33
00:03:15,000 --> 00:03:16,000
Come on.

34
00:03:17,000 --> 00:03:34,000
I pledge allegiance to the flag of the United States of America, and to the republic for which it stands, one nation, under God, indivisible, with liberty and justice for all.

35
00:03:34,000 --> 00:03:35,000
Amen.

36
00:03:35,000 --> 00:03:37,000
Excellent. Morning announcements.

37
00:03:38,000 --> 00:03:47,000
There's been a problem with some people sharing copier codes. Your copier code is a distinct 21-digit number that is unique to you, and you only. Okay? Don't share it.

38
00:03:48,000 --> 00:03:51,000
Joe Bennett, our CEO, will be here today for a high-level meeting involving Gabe and myself.

39
00:03:51,000 --> 00:03:52,000
Ooh, about what?

40
00:03:53,000 --> 00:03:54,000
That's on a need-to-know basis.

41
00:03:54,000 --> 00:03:56,000
I thought I needed to know for your calendar.

42
00:03:57,000 --> 00:03:58,000
General meet and greet.

43
00:03:58,000 --> 00:04:05,000
So I expect you to be on your best behavior, which means none of you will be insubordinate, nor will you foment insurrection.

44
00:04:05,000 --> 00:04:09,000
Question. If we've already fomented insurrection, may we be grandfathered in?

45
00:04:10,000 --> 00:04:11,000
Define foment.

46
00:04:12,000 --> 00:04:13,000
You define foment.

47
00:04:19,000 --> 00:04:21,000
Please take note of the new color-coding system.

48
00:04:21,000 --> 00:04:26,000
I will convince Joe to make me permanent manager by raising efficiency. No conference room meetings, no internet.

49
00:04:28,000 --> 00:04:35,000
This is a high-powered cell phone jammer I got off the black market. Although if I keep it too close to my genitals, I could have children with freakish mutations or powers.

50
00:04:44,000 --> 00:04:45,000
Aha!

51
